<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="being-vi">being <strong><em>vi</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'biːɪŋ/    美 /'biːɪŋ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-be-ing">1.★ <strong>[be的-ing形式]：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>用于分词短语或独立结构：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Being badly wounded, the whale soon died. 
由于受伤严重，那条鲸鱼很快就死了。</p><footer>人教⑦ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There being no buses, we had to take a taxi.
没有公交车了，我们只好乘出租车。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>用作动名词：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Being happy is the key to a fun-filled life. 
保持快乐是生活充满乐趣的关键。</p><footer>北师大① – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She hated being in front of other people. 
她不喜欢抛头露面。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>用于进行时的被动语态：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The matter was being discussed. 
当时正在讨论这件事。</p></div></div>